# The Shattered Isles

The world of Blades in the Dark (pp. 308–309). The sun was shattered in the cataclysm; the world lives in darkness behind lightning barriers, on seas of black ink. "This was once a storybook fantasy world of magic and wonders, which was destroyed and an industrial civilization was built on top of the ruins" (p. 308).

## Lands (p. 308)

- **[[Akoros]]** — petrified forests, rocky hills; the Imperial heartland. Home of [[Doskvol]].
- **Skovlan** — cold mountains, rough tundra; last holdout against Imperial control (Unity War, 809–845 IE). Includes **Lockport**, the factory town that processes 90% of the leviathan blood; poisoned by toxic fumes and acid rain (pp. 238, 290).
- **Severos** — windswept plains; outside the coastal Imperial cities, free tribes scavenge the deathlands on ghost-hunting horses.
- **Iruvia** — black deserts, obsidian mountains, volcanoes; some say demons openly hold positions of power.
- **The Dagger Isles** — tropical archipelago turned dark and twisted by the cataclysm; corsairs and merchants living without lightning barriers.
- **Tycheros** — far off beyond the northern Void Sea; people say the Tycherosi have demon blood.

The core book details only Doskvol; other cities are essentially map names (p. 309), with Lockport the lone exception.
